    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Pineapple Juice</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 ripe pineapple, peeled, cored, and chopped</li>
            <li>Water</li>
            <li>Optional: Sweetener of your choice (sugar, honey, agave syrup), to taste</li>
            <li>Ice cubes for serving</li>
            <li>Mint leaves for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Pineapple Juice</li>
            <li>Beverage</li>
            <li>Fruit Juice</li>
            <li>Refreshing</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Place the chopped pineapple in a blender.</li>
            <li>Add enough water to cover the pineapple pieces.</li>
            <li>Blend until smooth.</li>
            <li>Strain the pineapple mixture through a fine-mesh sieve or cheesecloth to extract the juice.</li>
            <li>Press the solids to extract more liquid.</li>
            <li>Taste the pineapple juice and add sweetener if desired, stirring until it dissolves.</li>
            <li>Chill the pineapple juice in the refrigerator.</li>
            <li>Serve cold over ice, garnished with mint leaves.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your refreshing Pineapple Juice!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

